# Before starting:
- Have Python installed in your computer.
- Install Microsoft Visual Studio C++ Build Tools for Windows from this website: https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/downloads/#build-tools-for-visual-studio-2022
- Install CMake from this website (choose windows x64 installer) : https://cmake.org/download/
- When CMake is finished installing, open up the msi file, and select "yes" to making CMake a PATH variable
- Open a new Windows terminal
- pip install virtualenv


# Installing the repo:
- git clone https://github.com/mitmedialab/LM_workshop_activities.git (you can this repository in the folder you want)
- cd LM_workshop_activities
- virtualenv â€”python=python3 python (if you run this once, you don't have to run it again in other times you access this repository/ folder)
- .\python\Scripts\activate (to run the virtual environment since source activate is for unix)
- pip install -r requirements.txt


# To run the repo every time:
In Windows native terminal do the following:
- cd into LM_workshop_activities
- .\python\Scripts\activate
To run certain sessions, follow the README instructions in each session folder
